There is no support for parallel testing with `chisel3.iotesters` (&quot;Chisel Testers&quot;). However, there is support for parallel testing with the new testing framework: [`chisel3.testers` (&quot;Chisel Testers2&quot;)](https://github.com/ucb-bar/chisel-testers2).

This adds support for `fork`, `join`, and `parallel` constructs. A concise example is testing a queue by [forking both the enqueueing and dequeueing](https://github.com/ucb-bar/chisel-testers2/blob/5025e93f7940fc458c4d08937f5bcfb7d4bdf338/src/test/scala/chisel3/tests/QueueTest.scala#L46): 

```scala
it should &quot;work with a combinational queue&quot; in {
  test(new PassthroughQueue(UInt(8.W))) { c =&gt;
    c.in.initSource()
    c.in.setSourceClock(c.clock)
    c.out.initSink()
    c.out.setSinkClock(c.clock)

    fork {
      c.in.enqueueSeq(Seq(42.U, 43.U, 44.U))
    }.fork {
      c.out.expectDequeueSeq(Seq(42.U, 43.U, 44.U))
    }.join()
  }
}
```

For an additional example, see the `chisel-template` file [`GcdTesters2.scala`](https://github.com/freechipsproject/chisel-template/blob/d37a3371a575570225af82d0064bdb845005d47a/src/test/scala/gcd/GcdTesters2.scala).

